The bus is gasping and shuddering its way down the potholed street, causing my fellow passengers to tut and grumble. The irritating 'tssk, tssk, tssk' tinny drumbeat from someone's iPod is seeping through the cacophony of yells from school children exchanging insults at the back. Outside the bus, a police siren is wailing.

But what do I care? I am cocooned in the land of nod, my head engulfed by a huge sound-proofed cushion that resembles a giant balaclava crossed with an old-fashioned diving helmet, with just my nose and mouth on display.

Out there it may be chaos, but in here I am napping in style. Of sorts.

